sec.p:
Justified by the imminent scarcity of energy sources based on conventional fossil fuels, the recent rise of metal halide perovskites (MHP defined by ABX3) as alternative of low cost photovoltaic material has excited the community centered around silicon, which has been considered the principal element in solar cells1–5. MHP based on the use of lead iodide (PbI3−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
