As first attempt to determine the stability of a hibrid perovskite from a specific composition, the Goldschmidt’s tolerance factor (t) is a geometric parameter initially used to predict the ability to form a 3D perovskite45, which empirically lie into 0.80<t<1.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
