Our results indicated that the metal atomic size plays an important role on the pseudo-cubic properties of the pure perovskites, e.g., as the similar local distortions for the MAPbI3 and MASnI3 octahedrals since their metals have almost the same atomic size. As such, the MAPb1−xSnxI3 alloy presents lattice parameters in good agreement with the Vegard’s law for the whole range of compositions, wherein the alloy adopts a random PbI3−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
